Do not seek to follow in the footsteps of the wise. Seek what they sought.


21. A mind is like a parachute — it only works when open.


22. Common sense is not so common.


23. To know others is intelligence; to know yourself is true wisdom.


24. One who is not courageous enough to take risks will accomplish nothing.


25. Knowledge is power, but wisdom is using it well.


26. Do not argue with a fool — onlookers may not be able to tell the difference.


27. Life is not about finding yourself; it’s about creating yourself.


28. Sometimes you win, sometimes you learn.


29. The wise don’t wait for opportunity — they create it.


30. Even a fool, when silent, is considered wise.


31. Learn as if you will live forever, live as if you will die tomorrow.


32. Don’t let your victories make you arrogant or your failures make you bitter.


33. He who conquers himself is the mightiest warrior.


34. A goal without a plan is just a wish.


35. The man who moves a mountain begins by carrying away small stones.


36. Better a diamond with a flaw than a pebble without.


37. Happiness depends on ourselves.


38. Do not be wise in words, be wise in deeds.


39. The art of being wise is knowing what to overlook.


40. To avoid criticism: say nothing, do nothing, be nothing.


41. Educating the mind without educating the heart is no education at all.


42. The fool talks, the wise man listens.


43. A man’s true wealth is the good he does in this world.


44. Beware of false knowledge; it is more dangerous than ignorance.


45. The measure of wisdom is how calm you stay in the storm.


46. What we achieve inwardly will change outer reality.


47. Don’t raise your voice, improve your argument.


48. Your future is created by what you do today, not tomorrow.


49. Humility is the solid foundation of all virtues.


50. Wisdom is knowing the right path to take; integrity is taking it.


51. Worrying does not take away tomorrow’s troubles — it takes away today’s peace.


52. Great minds discuss ideas; average minds discuss events; small minds discuss people.


53. When you know better, you do better.


54. He who opens a school door closes a prison.


55. The fool speaks because he has to say something; the wise speaks because he has something to say.


56. Don’t ruin a good today by thinking about a bad yesterday.


57. A stumble may prevent a fall.


58. Not everything that is faced can be changed, but nothing can be changed until it is faced.


59. An investment in knowledge pays the best interest.


60. Do not regret growing older; it is a privilege denied to many.


61. The wise make more opportunities than they find.


62. Life is really simple, but we insist on making it complicated.


63. A journey of a thousand miles begins with a single step.


64. The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now.


65. Don’t let schooling interfere with your education.


66. The past cannot be changed, but the future is in your power.


67. Better to light a candle than curse the darkness.


68. The only real failure is the failure to try.


69. Even the longest day has its end.


70. The wise man knows he knows nothing.


71. Your attitude, not your aptitude, determines your altitude.


72. Do not let what you cannot do interfere with what you can do.


73. Fall seven times and stand up eight.


74. The one who asks a question is a fool for a minute; the one who does not ask is a fool for life.


75. He who fears he will suffer, already suffers what he fears.


76. Sometimes the wrong choices bring us to the right places.


77. The greatest wealth is to live content with little.


78. Every saint has a past, every sinner has a future.


79. Don’t gain the world and lose your soul.


80. Where there is no vision, the people perish.


81. Life is 10% what happens to you and 90% how you react to it.


82. What you seek is seeking you.


83. Respect yourself and others will respect you.


84. He who has a why can bear almost any how.


85. Change your thoughts and you change your world.


86. Mistakes are proof that you are trying.


87. The man who asks a question is a fool for a minute, the man who does not ask is a fool for life.


88. The best way to predict the future is to create it.


89. Life is not measured by the number of breaths we take, but by the moments that take our breath away.


90. Knowledge is learning something every day. Wisdom is letting go of something every day.


91. Anger is a wind that blows out the lamp of the mind.


92. Kindness is a language the deaf can hear and the blind can see.


93. He who cannot obey himself will be commanded.


94. Never let success get to your head and never let failure get to your heart.


95. Do not dwell in the past, do not dream of the future, concentrate the mind on the present moment.


96. If you chase two rabbits, you will catch neither.


97. Peace begins with a smile.


98. The weak can never forgive. Forgiveness is the attribute of the strong.


99. Do not waste your energy on revenge. The people who hurt you will face their own karma.


100. What you do today can improve all your tomorrows.
